column1: # Spodoptera experiment 2.  ~ 3 day duration. Started with 2nd instar larva (greenish tint). I initiated this because I was worried the first experiment using late first instar larva may yield reliable results because of delicate larva. This experiment seemed too wet (better to squeeze out cotton completely prior). Also it seemed at times herbivores didn't have access to tissue if it was facing down and directly touching the wet cotton. This may have deterred herbivores haphazardly or be biased because this was less likely to happen with larger leaves. Began weighing larva on July 24, 2013.

column8: 90% leaf rot, but there was herbivory from spodop
